Subject: [PATCH] xe/Kconfig: Add CONFIG_DRM_GPUVM configuration option

The Intel XE GPU driver depends on the DRM_GPUVM subsystem which was
introduced in Linux kernel 6.8. For kernels prior to 6.8, the
DRM_GPUVM functionality needs to be backported to provide the GPUVM
management framework that XE relies on.

Reference:
    b06d47be7c83
    drm/xe: Port Xe to GPUVA

Signed-off-by: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Kconfig | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Kconfig b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Kconfig
index 3372998..b2d9c34 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Kconfig
@@ -1,4 +1,11 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
+config DRM_GPUVM
+	tristate "Enable Xe-specific DRM GPUVM support"
+	depends on DRM
+	default m
+	help
+	  GPU-VM representation providing helpers to manage a GPUs virtual
+          address space (Xe-specific backport version)
 config DRM_XE
 	tristate "Intel Xe Graphics"
 	depends on DRM && PCI && MMU && (m || (y && KUNIT=y))
